Bank of England Rate-Rise Bets Pushed Back to April, Sonia Forwards Show

-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 
2011-06-07T07:28:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/bank-of-england-rate-rise-bets-pushed-back-to-april-sonia-forwards-show.html
Investors pushed back bets that the
 Bank of England  will increase  interest rates  to April, forward
contracts on the sterling overnight interbank average show.  The central bank will raise its benchmark rate by 25 basis
points in April, to 0.75 percent, data from Tullett Prebon Plc
shows. As recently as yesterday, traders were betting on an
increase in February, the data showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in London at 
 pdobson2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Daniel Tilles at 
 dtilles@bloomberg.net  